summary: Has-been rock star Ethan Brand is attempting a comeback when a former groupie tells him he has a 13-year-old daughter, Janie, and leaves her in his care. Janie must then convince the hedonistic Ethan to reform and accept his responsibilities.

title: Blue Car
cast: David Strathairn, Agnes Bruckner, Margaret Colin, Frances Fisher, A.J. Buckley, Regan Arnold, Sarah Beuhler, Dustin Sterling, Michael Joseph Thomas Ward, Wayne Armstrong
summary: A troubled teenager gets writing help -- and much-needed attention -- from her English teacher, but she doesn't stop to think what he wants from her.

summary: Scientist Jack Griffin (Claude Rains) terrorizes the British village of Ipping in this classic horror film. By the time Griffin confides in friends Dr. Kemp (William Harrigan) and Flora (Gloria Stuart), it's too late -- the drug has turned him into a homicidal maniac who must be hunted down.

summary: When two brothers discover a dead body and millions of dollars in a downed plane, they plot to split the loot -- until things go murderously awry.

summary: Thirteen years after Aurora lost her only child to cancer, her grandson is now in jail, so she sets her sights on her rebellious granddaughter.

title: The Ghost and the Darkness
cast: Michael Douglas, Val Kilmer, Tom Wilkinson, John Kani, Bernard Hill, Brian McCardie, Emily Mortimer, Om Puri
summary: While working for a railroad baron in colonial Uganda, engineer John Patterson finds his construction efforts stymied by a series of lion attacks. Grizzled hunter Charles Remington is called in to head the desperate effort to kill the animals.

title: Exodus

summary: Neofascist politician Pharaoh Mann clears the streets of undesirables, confining them to a ghetto called Dreamland. But when Mann's adopted son discovers that his real parents are imprisoned refugees, he attempts to help them escape.

title: Wild China
cast: Bernard Hill
summary: This six-part series uncovers some of the most exotic and uncharted natural habitats hidden within the vast and diverse topography of China, including Yunnan's forests, the Tibetan plateau, the Silk Road and the Mongol steppes.

Obsessively searching for God, Sybok hijacks the Enterprise and sets a course for the center of the galaxy. The film marks Shatner's directorial debut.

Co-starring David Warner as a medium who helps the duo communicate with the dead, this horror film digs up plenty of disturbing secrets from the past.

title: The Pink Panther 2

summary: Blundering Inspector Jacques Clouseau joins a team of equally incompetent detectives to foil a thief who's been heisting historical artifacts.

Scott, and arguably the most recognizable film critic of all time, Roger Ebert.

summary: Quentin Tarantino's directorial debut is raw, violent, often mimicked -- and unforgettable. A botched robbery indicates a police informant, and the pressure mounts in the aftermath at a warehouse. Crime begets violence as the survivors unravel.

title: Thelma & Louise
cast: Susan Sarandon, Geena Davis, Harvey Keitel, Michael Madsen, Brad Pitt, Christopher McDonald, Stephen Tobolowsky, Timothy Carhart, Lucinda Jenney, Jason Beghe
summary: Fed up with her boyfriend, live-wire Arkansas waitress Louise Sawyer (Susan Sarandon) persuades her friend Thelma Dickinson (Geena Davis), a naïve housewife burdened with a negligent, sexist husband, to hit the road with her for a simple weekend of freedom. But after accidentally killing a man, the two friends wind up outlaws blazing a cathartic trail across America. Callie Khouri won an Academy Award for Best Screenplay.

title: Blue in the Face
cast: Harvey Keitel, Lou Reed, Michael J. Fox, Roseanne Barr, Mel Gorham, Jim Jarmusch, Lily Tomlin, Jared Harris, Giancarlo Esposito, Malik Yoba
director: Wayne Wang, Paul Auster, Harvey Wang
summary: As a stand-alone movie or as a companion to the critically acclaimed Wayne Wang movie Smoke, this faux-documentary captures improvised scenes using the same cast as Wang's movie and others who dropped by during filming.

title: Smoke
cast: William Hurt, Harvey Keitel, Stockard Channing, Ashley Judd, Giancarlo Esposito, José Zúñiga, Stephen Gevedon, Jared Harris, Harold Perrineau, Forest Whitaker
summary: A Brooklyn cigar store anchors the vignettes that make up this lyrical Wayne Wang movie written by famous author Paul Auster. Auggie (Harvey Keitel), the store manager, is surprised by a visit from his ex-wife, who says their daughter is in trouble. Rashid (Harold Perrineau Jr.), a runaway searching for his father (Forest Whittaker), saves Auggie's customer, Paul (William Hurt), from being hit by a car, and changes his life forever.

title: The Piano
cast: Holly Hunter, Harvey Keitel, Sam Neill, Anna Paquin, Kerry Walker, Genevieve Lemon, Tungia Baker, Ian Mune
summary: Holly Hunter stars as Ada McGrath, a mute but strong-willed 19th-century Scottish expatriate who arrives in New Zealand with her daughter (Anna Paquin) and her beloved piano in tow. Although betrothed to a landowner (Sam Neill), she's pulled into an affair with a laborer (Harvey Keitel). Hunter and Paquin both won Oscars for their performances in this haunting drama from writer-director Jane Campion.

title: Bad Lieutenant
cast: Harvey Keitel, Victor Argo, Paul Calderon, Robin Burrows, Frankie Thorn, Leonard L. Thomas, Victoria Bastel, Paul Hipp
summary: This gritty, visceral crime drama puts an out-of-control police lieutenant on a collision course with disaster. A survivor of the streets, this junkie, thief and killer is forced to confront his private demons when he investigates the rape of a nun.

title: Clockers
cast: Harvey Keitel, John Turturro, Delroy Lindo, Mekhi Phifer, Isaiah Washington, Keith David, Pee Wee Love, Spike Lee, Martin Scorsese
summary: Strike is from the mean streets, working his way up in the drug rackets. When a local kingpin tips him off to an opportunity for advancement, a rival dealer is killed, and Strike gets caught between two homicide detectives. Directed by Spike Lee, produced by Martin Scorsese and adapted from a Richard Price novel, Clockers was "one of 1995's most powerful films," according to Jeffrey Lyons of Sneak Previews.

title: Fairy Tale: A True Story
cast: Florence Hoath, Elizabeth Earl, Paul McGann, Phoebe Nicholls, Peter O'Toole, Bill Nighy, Bob Peck, Tim McInnerny, Mel Gibson, Harvey Keitel
summary: In this charming fantasy, two precocious cousins discover sprites in their garden -- and to prove the pixies exist, the girls produce photographic evidence that draws worldwide attention. But are the fairies real, or is it all a hoax?

title: The Last Temptation of Christ
cast: Willem Dafoe, Harvey Keitel, Verna Bloom, Barbara Hershey, Barry Miller, Gary Basaraba, Irvin Kershner, Victor Argo, Paul Herman, John Lurie
summary: Nikos Kazantzakis's landmark novel comes to life in director Martin Scorsese's moving, spiritual and highly controversial film that challenges the Christian notion that Jesus (Willem Dafoe) was both a man and a divine being. With an all-star cast that includes Harvey Keitel, Barbara Hershey, Harry Dean Stanton and David Bowie, the film portrays Jesus as unmistakably human, susceptible to the desires, doubts and temptations that all men face.

title: A Beginner's Guide to Endings
cast: Scott Caan, Paulo Costanzo, Jason Jones, Tricia Helfer, J.K. Simmons, Harvey Keitel
summary: When their father kicks the bucket, three unsuspecting brothers learn that their dad's gambling and reckless ways have doomed them all to die. With only a few days left to live, they set out to try to make amends. But time's running out quickly.

title: Monkey Trouble
cast: Thora Birch, Harvey Keitel, Mimi Rogers, Christopher McDonald, Alison Elliott, Victor Argo, Remy Ryan, Adam LaVorgna, Jo Champa, John Lafayette
summary: When Eva (Thora Birch) secretly adopts a mischievous capuchin monkey, her life turns upside down in this slapstick family comedy. Eva's mother (Mimi Rogers) and allergic stepfather (Christopher McDonald) raise objections, especially when the animal begins stealing everything in sight, but Eva is concerned about protecting her new pet from Azro (Harvey Keitel), who wants to find him and use him as part of an important robbery.

title: The Outsider
cast: Woody Allen, Robert Downey Jr., Neve Campbell, James Toback, Harvey Keitel, Mike Tyson, Jim Brown, John Calley, Damon Dash, Roger Ebert
summary: Following maverick writer-director James Toback through the process of making his 2004 drama When Will I Be Loved, this documentary provides a fascinating look inside the world of filmmaking. Toback, whose previous screenplays include The Gambler and Bugsy, shot the movie in 12 days without a script and battled to get it released. Woody Allen, Robert Downey Jr., Harvey Keitel, Brooke Shields, Roger Ebert and many others discuss Toback and his work.

title: The Young Americans
cast: Harvey Keitel, Iain Glen, John Wood, Terence Rigby, Keith Allen, Craig Kelly, Thandie Newton, Viggo Mortensen, Dave Duffy, Geoffrey McGivern
summary: In London, the growing presence of a unique mob of young American drug dealers prompts Scotland Yard to recruit DEA agent John Harris to combat them.

title: The Last Godfather
cast: Hyung-rae Shim, Harvey Keitel, Jocelin Donahue, Michael Rispoli, Jason Mewes, John Pinette, Josh Rosenthal, Paul Hipp, Jon Polito, Blake Clark, Debra Mooney, Logan Shea, Jack Kehler
summary: When he discovers that Younggu may be his illegitimate son, an aging American mob boss decides to groom the lad to succeed him as the next godfather.

title: The Grey Zone
cast: David Arquette, Steve Buscemi, Harvey Keitel, Allan Corduner, Mira Sorvino, Natasha Lyonne, Daniel Benzali, David Chandler, Lisa Benavides, Henry Stram
summary: Based on actual events, this is the staggeringly powerful story of Auschwitz's 12th Sonderkommando -- one of 13 "special squads" of Jewish prisoners forced by the Nazis to help exterminate fellow Jews in exchange for a few more months of life.

title: Adore
cast: Naomi Watts, Robin Wright, Xavier Samuel, James Frecheville, Ben Mendelsohn, Sophie Lowe, Jessica Tovey, Gary Sweet, Alyson Standen, Skye Sutherland
summary: In this seaside drama adapted from a novella by Nobel Prize winner Doris Lessing, two lifelong friends who fall in love with each other's teenage sons must carry out their affairs in relative secrecy.

title: Gettin' Square
cast: Sam Worthington, David Wenham, Timothy Spall, Freya Stafford, Gary Sweet, David Roberts, David Field, Mitchell Butel, Garry Waddell, John Brumpton
summary: Determined to stay on the straight and narrow, parolees Barry (Sam Worthington) and Spit (David Wenham) get restaurant jobs -- where they end up tangling with local gangster Chicka (Gary Sweet). Barry and Spit's employer (Timothy Spall) is also a reformed ex-con, and together, the three conspire to bring down the crime boss. This much-nominated Australian comedy also stars Freya Stafford and Steven Tandy.

title: Nightmares
cast: Jenny Neumann, Gary Sweet, Nina Landis, Max Phipps, John Michael Howson, Edmund Pegge, Sue Jones, Briony Behets, Maureen Edwards, Peter Tulloch
summary: This dark and bloody thriller begins with a little girl trying to stop her mother from carrying on with a man in a car -- with horrific results. Years later, the same girl is acting in a play that is hit by a rash of brutal slayings.

title: Girl, Interrupted
cast: Winona Ryder, Angelina Jolie, Whoopi Goldberg, Clea DuVall, Brittany Murphy, Elisabeth Moss, Jared Leto, Jeffrey Tambor, Vanessa Redgrave, Angela Bettis
summary: Diagnosed with a disorder, Susanna Kaysen is sent to a mental institution, where she enters the skewed world of people who truly belong on the inside. Angelina Jolie won an Oscar for her portrayal of a seductive patient who befriends Kaysen.

title: The Long Walk Home
cast: Sissy Spacek, Whoopi Goldberg, Dwight Schultz, Ving Rhames, Dylan Baker, Erika Alexander, Lexi Randall, Richard Habersham, Chelcie Ross, Dan Butler
summary: Sissy Spacek stars as Miriam Thompson, a Montgomery, Ala., housewife who finds herself in the midst of a civil rights revolution when she helps her black maid, Odessa (Whoopi Goldberg), during the infamous bus boycott of the 1950s. When Miriam discovers Odessa is forced to walk the 9 miles to her house and back, she volunteers to give Odessa a ride -- much to the dismay of Miriam's husband and social circle.

title: Sarafina!
cast: Leleti Khumalo, Whoopi Goldberg, Miriam Makeba, John Kani, Dumisani Dlamini, Mbongeni Ngema, Sipho Kunene, Tertius Meintjes, Robert Whitehead, Somizi Mhlongo
summary: Catch this inspirational story about a girl battling the oppression of apartheid in South Africa. Schoolgirl Sarafina (Leleti Khumalo) lives in Soweto. Her mother lives in Johannesburg, where she works for a white family. Missing her mother, Sarafina puts her energy into fighting for freedom. When police shoot and kill protesting students supporting their teacher (Whoopi Goldberg), Sarafina is arrested as a demonstrator and faces prison and torture.

title: Soapdish
cast: Sally Field, Kevin Kline, Robert Downey Jr., Cathy Moriarty, Elisabeth Shue, Whoopi Goldberg, Teri Hatcher, Garry Marshall, Kathy Najimy, Arne Nannestad
summary: Soap opera star Celeste Talbert gets desperate when she finds out that her rival, Montana Moorehead, has been trying to get producer David Barnes to write her off the show. And since Barnes has eyes for Montana, Celeste must scramble to keep her job.

title: Ghost
cast: Patrick Swayze, Demi Moore, Whoopi Goldberg, Tony Goldwyn, Susan Breslau, Martina Degnan, Rick Aviles, Vincent Schiavelli, Angelina Estrada, Phil Leeds
summary: Gothamites Sam and Molly see their romance shattered when a street thug kills Sam during a mugging. But love endures beyond the grave when a spectral Sam learns that Molly is in danger, and he must find a way to warn her before she suffers his fate.

title: Get Bruce!
cast: Bruce Vilanch, Robin Williams, Bette Midler, Nathan Lane, Whoopi Goldberg, Lily Tomlin, Raquel Welch, Shirley MacLaine, Florence Henderson, Steven Seagal
summary: This documentary delves into the life and work of comedy writer Bruce Vilanch, a behind-the-scenes Hollywood legend. Vilanch has written for the Oscar, Emmy, Tony and Grammy awards shows, as well as one-liners for Bette Midler and Whoopi Goldberg.

title: Mia and the Migoo
cast: James Woods, Matthew Modine, Whoopi Goldberg
summary: When a construction accident traps her father near a remote lake, Mia journeys through the jungle to rescue him in this animated feature. There, she encounters the Migou, fantastic beings who protect a sacred tree that safeguards all life on Earth.

title: Monkeybone
cast: Brendan Fraser, Bridget Fonda, John Turturro, Chris Kattan, Giancarlo Esposito, Rose McGowan, Dave Foley, Megan Mullally, Whoopi Goldberg, Shawnee Free Jones
summary: Cartoonist Stu Miley finds success with his raucous creation, a troublemaking simian named Monkeybone. But after a car accident puts Stu in a coma, he finds himself face-to-face with Monkeybone in a freakish netherworld called Downtown.

title: Being Elmo: A Puppeteer's Journey
cast: Kevin Clash, Whoopi Goldberg
summary: Beloved by millions of children, Elmo is an international icon. But few people know the soft-spoken man behind the furry red monster: Kevin Clash. Narrated by Whoopi Goldberg, this documentary follows Clash's remarkable career as a puppeteer.

title: The Little Engine That Could
cast: Corbin Bleu, Jamie Lee Curtis, Whoopi Goldberg, Dominic Scott Kay, Brenda Song, Alyson Stoner, Patrick Warburton, Jeff Bennett
summary: A timeless children's classic comes roaring to life in this star-studded animated tale of a train who overcomes every obstacle by repeating the words "I think I can, I think I can." Along the way, he climbs new heights and finds new friends.

title: Pee-wee's Playhouse: Christmas Special
cast: Paul Reubens, Annette Funicello, Frankie Avalon, Grace Jones, k.d. lang, Dinah Shore, Little Richard, Cher, Eadie del Rubio, Magic Johnson, Elena del Rubio, Zsa Zsa Gabor, Milly del Rubio, Whoopi Goldberg, Oprah Winfrey, Joan Rivers
summary: Amid an avalanche of stars, Pee-wee straps on his ice skates and glides into the holiday season with Christmas cards, carols ... and Charo.

title: Amistad
cast: Morgan Freeman, Nigel Hawthorne, Anthony Hopkins, Djimon Hounsou, Matthew McConaughey, David Paymer, Pete Postlethwaite, Stellan Skarsgård, Razaaq Adoti, Abu Bakaar Fofanah
summary: Steven Spielberg directed this story about the 1839 revolt aboard Spanish slave ship La Amistad and the uprising's tragic aftermath.

title: Tarzan
cast: Tony Goldwyn, Minnie Driver, Glenn Close, Brian Blessed, Nigel Hawthorne, Rosie O'Donnell, Lance Henriksen, Wayne Knight
summary: After being shipwrecked off the African coast, a lone child grows up in the wild, and is destined to become lord of the jungle.

title: Madeline
cast: Frances McDormand, Nigel Hawthorne, Hatty Jones, Ben Daniels, Arturo Venegas, Stéphane Audran, Katia Caballero, Chantal Neuwirth, Kristian de la Osa, Clare Thomas
summary: To save her boarding school from the real estate market, a mischievous French girl uses her wits to discourage prospective buyers.

title: Babysitters Beware
cast: Trenton Rogers, Rico Rodriguez, Chris Cleveland, Brittany Renee Finamore, Kate Orsini, Taylor Negron, Luis Anthony, Danny Trejo, Dee Wallace, Mercedes Colon
summary: Danny Parker (Trenton Rogers) is sick of being stuck with baby-sitters while his mom and dad, Wendy (Kate Orsini) and Jim (Chris Cleveland), go off to meetings, so when he finds out about the "no-sit" list of kids no one wants to look after, he's determined to join. In this family comedy, Parker doesn't have a bad bone in him, but with tips from his pal, Marco (Rico Rodriguez), and lots of practice, the model son turns into a perfect terror.

title: Maximum Overdrive
cast: Emilio Estevez, Pat Hingle, Laura Harrington, Yeardley Smith, John Short, Ellen McElduff, J.C. Quinn, Christopher Murney, Frankie Faison, Holter Graham
summary: When a mysterious comet passes close to Earth, machines everywhere take on murderous minds of their own. But humans won't give up without a fight.

title: The Thomas Crown Affair
cast: Pierce Brosnan, Rene Russo, Denis Leary, Ben Gazzara, Frankie Faison, Fritz Weaver, Charles Keating, Mark Margolis, Faye Dunaway, Michael Lombard
summary: This remake of the 1968 classic showcases Pierce Brosnan as the titular billionaire who, for kicks, would rather steal works of art than buy them.

title: The Silence of the Lambs
cast: Jodie Foster, Anthony Hopkins, Scott Glenn, Ted Levine, Anthony Heald, Brooke Smith, Diane Baker, Kasi Lemmons, Frankie Faison
summary: In this adaptation of Thomas Harris's novel, FBI trainee Clarice Starling ventures into a maximum-security asylum to pick the diseased brain of Hannibal Lecter, hoping the psychiatrist turned homicidal cannibal can help her catch a serial killer.

title: Albino Alligator
cast: Matt Dillon, Faye Dunaway, Gary Sinise, William Fichtner, Viggo Mortensen, John Spencer, Skeet Ulrich, Frankie Faison, Melinda McGraw, M. Emmet Walsh
summary: Kevin Spacey made his directing debut with this edgy crime drama about a trio of small-time hoods (Matt Dillon, Gary Sinise and William Fichtner) fleeing after a bungled robbery in New Orleans. They hole up in a basement bar, taking five people hostage while trying to determine their next move as the feds and a Special Weapons and Tactics team swarm outside. The great cast includes Faye Dunaway, Joe Mantegna and Viggo Mortensen.

title: Coming to America
cast: Eddie Murphy, Arsenio Hall, James Earl Jones, John Amos, Madge Sinclair, Shari Headley, Paul Bates, Eriq La Salle, Frankie Faison, Vanessa Bell Calloway
summary: Discontented with his pampered life, an African prince heads to America to find someone who will fall for him, not his riches. Joined by his trusty sidekick, the prince plunges into a job at a fast-food chain -- and romance with the boss's daughter.

title: Oxygen
cast: Maura Tierney, Adrien Brody, James Naughton, Laila Robins, Terry Kinney, Paul Calderon, Dylan Baker, Olek Krupa, Frankie Faison, Slavko Stimac
summary: Madeline Foster (Maura Tierney) is an NYPD detective with a drinking problem and a penchant for rough sex in this police thriller that has her investigating the kidnapping of a businessman's wife. With the kidnapper threatening to kill his hostage if ransom isn't delivered within 24 hours, Madeline deduces she's dealing with the notorious "Harry Houdini" (Adrien Brody) -- so named for his uncanny ability to avoid capture.

title: Hannibal
cast: Anthony Hopkins, Julianne Moore, Gary Oldman, Ray Liotta, Frankie Faison, Giancarlo Giannini, Francesca Neri, Zeljko Ivanek, David Andrews, Francis Guinan
summary: Anthony Hopkins returns as serial killer Hannibal Lecter -- one of the great villains in screen history -- in this riveting sequel that finds his only surviving victim trying to draw Lecter out of hiding by using FBI agent Clarice Starling as bait.

title: The Langoliers
cast: Patricia Wettig, Dean Stockwell, David Morse, Mark Lindsay Chapman, Frankie Faison, Baxter Harris, Kimber Riddle, Christopher Collet, Kate Maberly, Bronson Pinchot
summary: Ten people awake on a red-eye flight from Los Angeles to discover that the other passengers, the flight crew and the pilots have disappeared. After a passenger (David Morse) manages to land the plane, the small group of survivors soon makes a startling discovery. Not only are they alone on the plane -- they're alone on the planet. The sole sound on Earth comes from the mysterious Langoliers, who are systematically destroying everything in their path.

title: White Chicks
cast: Shawn Wayans, Marlon Wayans, Jaime King, Frankie Faison, Lochlyn Munro, John Heard, Busy Philipps, Terry Crews, Brittany Daniel, Eddie Velez
summary: After botching a drug bust, two black FBI agents find themselves consigned to baby-sitting a pair of empty-headed socialites -- who end up being the targets of kidnappers. To flush out the baddies, the men pose as the white party girls.

title: Cowgirls n' Angels
cast: Bailee Madison, James Cromwell, Jackson Rathbone, Alicia Witt, Kathleen Rose Perkins, Frankie Faison, Dora Madison Burge, Leslie-Anne Huff, Drew Waters, Noell Coet, Andrew Sensenig, Louanne Stephens
summary: When a feisty youngster seeks refuge with a troupe of female rodeo riders and their ornery leader, she finds both a new family and a grand passion.

title: The Third Wish
cast: Jenna Mattison, Sean Maguire, Armand Assante, Jennifer Blanc, Betty White, James Avery, Mindy Cohn, Robert Costanzo, Susan Egan, Ronnie Marmo
summary: A bookshop clerk goes from the proverbial rags to riches when she's granted three wishes after finding a rare first-edition copy of Charles Dickens's Great Expectations. But will her luck hold out after she makes that all-important third wish?

title: Air Bud: Golden Receiver
cast: Tim Conway, Michael Jeter, Wendy Makkena, Cynthia Stevenson, Kevin Zegers, Robert Costanzo, Perry Anzilotti, Tyler Thompson, Gregory Harrison, Nora Dunn
summary: Picking up where the original Air Bud left off, Josh is the owner of golden retriever Buddy, who now plays football instead of basketball. Josh reluctantly becomes his school's new quarterback, and Buddy catches the spirit and joins the team too.

title: Carol Channing: Larger Than Life
cast: Carol Channing, Harry Kullijian, Jerry Herman, Marge Champion, Bruce Vilanch, Lily Tomlin, Debbie Reynolds, Tippi Hedren, Bob Mackie, Betty Garrett
summary: The astonishing life of Carol Channing unfolds in this entertaining biopic, which captures the bold Broadway legend's outsize personality. Batting her lashes, Channing shares (in her trademark rasp) sweet and sour memories from her storied career.

title: Going Down in La-La Land
cast: Matthew Ludwinski, Allison Lane, Michael Medico, Casper Andreas, John Schile, Jesse Archer, Bruce Vilanch, Judy Tenuta, Alec Mapa
summary: Hunky actor Adam arrives in Los Angeles from New York, brimming with hope for a career in the movie business. His good looks draw the attention of agents and studio execs, and almost instantly, he begins to climb the ladder of fame -- or so it seems.

title: Walk a Mile in My Pradas
cast: Nathaniel Marston, Tom Archdeacon, Tom Arnold, Mike Starr, Dee Wallace, Bruce Vilanch, Kirsten Lea, Rick Karatas
summary: A magic Christmas ornament turns two men's lives upside down when homophobic Tony starts preferring men two weeks before his wedding and his gay co-worker Steve finds himself blossoming into a ladies' man.

title: I Am Divine
cast: John Waters, Ricki Lake, Mink Stole, Tab Hunter, Holly Woodlawn, Michael Musto, Bruce Vilanch, Mary Vivian Pearce
summary: This captivating documentary explores the life and work of filmmaker John Waters's muse: internationally celebrated drag superstar Divine.

title: Pride: The Gay and Lesbian Comedy Slam
cast: Bruce Vilanch, Alec Mapa, Sandra Valls, Scott Kennedy, Poppy Champlin
summary: Hosted by iconic comedy satirist Bruce Vilanch, this stand-up showcase features gay comics Poppy Champlin, Sandra Valls, Scott Kennedy and Alec Mapa.

title: Devil in a Blue Dress
cast: Denzel Washington, Tom Sizemore, Jennifer Beals, Don Cheadle, Maury Chaykin, Terry Kinney, Mel Winkler, Albert Hall, Lisa Nicole Carson, Jernard Burks
summary: In this compelling neo-noir set in 1948 Los Angeles, a stranger asks war veteran "Easy" Rawlins to help him locate a missing woman. But Rawlins gets more than he bargained for and soon becomes entangled in a murder mystery.

title: Hotel Rwanda
cast: Don Cheadle, Sophie Okonedo, Joaquin Phoenix, Nick Nolte, Desmond Dube, David O'Hara, Cara Seymour, Fana Mokoena, Hakeem Kae-Kazim, Tony Kgoroge
summary: Amid the holocaust of internecine tribal fighting in Rwanda that sees the savage butchering of hundreds of thousands of men, women and children, one ordinary hotel manager musters the courage to save more than 1,000 helpless refugees.

title: Mr. Mom
cast: Michael Keaton, Teri Garr, Fred Koehler, Taliesin Jaffe, Martin Mull, Ann Jillian, Jeffrey Tambor, Christopher Lloyd
summary: When Jack is laid off at the car factory, his wife takes a job at an advertising agency and leaves Jack at home to raise the kids.

title: Flight
cast: Denzel Washington, John Goodman, Don Cheadle, Melissa Leo, Brian Geraghty, Bruce Greenwood, Kelly Reilly, Tamara Tunie, Garcelle Beauvais, James Badge Dale
summary: After his amazing safe landing of a damaged passenger plane, an airline pilot is praised for the feat, but has private questions about what happened. Further, the government's inquiry into the causes soon puts the new hero's reputation at risk.

title: Colors
cast: Sean Penn, Robert Duvall, Maria Conchita Alonso, Randy Brooks, Grand L. Bush, Don Cheadle, Gerardo Mejia, Glenn Plummer, Rudy Ramos
summary: Veteran cop Bob Hodges has nothing but contempt for his new partner, fiery rookie Danny McGavin. But he gradually comes to appreciate Danny as they patrol the streets of East Los Angeles, where a gang war between the Crips and Bloods is escalating.

title: Things Behind the Sun
cast: Kim Dickens, Gabriel Mann, Aria Alpert, Ruben Anders, Rosanna Arquette, Eric Stoltz, Don Cheadle, Elizabeth Peña, Alison Folland, Patsy Kensit
summary: A rock journalist pitches a story about an underground singer-songwriter who makes a name for herself with a powerful song about rape. But his interest runs deeper than her music -- he has a personal connection to the crime.

title: A Man's Story
cast: Ozwald Boateng, Giorgio Armani, Michael Bay, Paul Bettany, Richard Branson, Gabriel Byrne, Don Cheadle, Daniel Day-Lewis, Laurence Fishburne, Jamie Foxx
summary: Celebrated menswear designer Ozwald Boateng is also a man of strong passions, as recorded in this revealing documentary filmed over 10 years. Boateng's personal challenges are contrasted with the elation his designs inspire at London Fashion Week.

title: Traffic
cast: Michael Douglas, Don Cheadle, Benicio Del Toro, Luis Guzmán, Dennis Quaid, Catherine Zeta-Jones, Steven Bauer, Benjamin Bratt, James Brolin, Erika Christensen
summary: Interlacing three disturbing snapshots of America's drug war, this Oscar-winning saga follows a U.S. drug czar who learns his daughter's an addict, a Mexican cop caught in a corrupt system and a housewife forced to take over the family drug business.

title: Reign Over Me
cast: Adam Sandler, Don Cheadle, Jada Pinkett Smith, Liv Tyler, Saffron Burrows, Donald Sutherland, Robert Klein, Melinda Dillon, Mike Binder, Jonathan Banks
summary: A chance meeting with his college roommate, now a family man, starts the recovery for a man still grieving the loss of his family on September 11.

title: American Dreamz
cast: Hugh Grant, Dennis Quaid, Mandy Moore, Willem Dafoe, Chris Klein, Jennifer Coolidge, Sam Golzari, Marcia Gay Harden, Seth Meyers, John Cho
summary: To get a reclusive president back in the limelight, his chief of staff books him as a guest judge on the hit talent show "American Dreamz."

title: Day Zero
cast: Elijah Wood, Chris Klein, Jon Bernthal, Ginnifer Goodwin, Elisabeth Moss, Ally Sheedy, Sofia Vassilieva, Zoe Lister Jones, John Rothman
summary: In an otherworldly America, the draft has been reinstated to fight the global war on terror, and a new generation is faced with military service. At the center of it all are three conflicted friends: a novelist, a corporate lawyer and a cab driver.

title: We Were Soldiers
cast: Mel Gibson, Madeleine Stowe, Greg Kinnear, Sam Elliott, Chris Klein, Keri Russell, Barry Pepper, Duong Don, Ryan Hurst, Robert Bagnell
summary: This Vietnam War epic tells the story of the Battle of Ia Drang, which pitted 450 U.S. soldiers against thousands of well-armed Vietnamese troops.

title: Authors Anonymous
cast: Kaley Cuoco, Chris Klein, Dennis Farina, Jonathan Bennett, Dylan Walsh, Teri Polo, Tricia Helfer, Jonathan Banks
summary: A band of unpublished writers who gather to gripe about their misfortunes must cope with the sudden success of a newcomer to their group.

title: Election
cast: Matthew Broderick, Reese Witherspoon, Chris Klein, Jessica Campbell, Phil Reeves, Molly Hagan, Delaney Driscoll, Mark Harelik, Colleen Camp, Frankie Ingrassia
summary: Tracy Flick appears to have the election for student council president sewn up until a teacher rounds up a worthy opponent: a popular football player.

title: The Wait
cast: Jena Malone, Chloë Sevigny, Luke Grimes, Devon Gearhart, Michael O'Keefe, Josh Hamilton, Lana Elizabeth Green, Henry Gummer, Trey Hansen, Karen Tolvstad
summary: Chloë Sevigny and Jena Malone play sisters struggling to cope with their mother's recent death in this Pacific Northwest-set supernatural drama. When a psychic predicts that the dearly departed will rise again, the sibs put off Mom's burial.

title: Saved!
cast: Mandy Moore, Jena Malone, Macaulay Culkin, Patrick Fugit, Heather Matarazzo, Eva Amurri Martino, Chad Faust, Elizabeth Thai, Mary-Louise Parker, Martin Donovan
summary: When Mary, a devout senior at a Christian high school, accidentally gets pregnant, she starts to see her peers and her faith in a whole new way in this darkly comic coming-of-age story that was produced by R.E.M. front man Michael Stipe.

title: The Dangerous Lives of Altar Boys
cast: Emile Hirsch, Kieran Culkin, Vincent D'Onofrio, Jena Malone, Jake Richardson, Tyler Long, Jodie Foster, Arthur Bridgers
summary: When a bunch of eighth-grade Catholic school students get caught drawing an obscene comic book, they seek revenge for their punishment -- and a reputation as school legends -- by planning a prank on the mean, one-legged nun who nabbed them.

title: Donnie Darko
cast: Jake Gyllenhaal, Jena Malone, Drew Barrymore, James Duval, Beth Grant, Maggie Gyllenhaal, Mary McDonnell, Holmes Osborne, Patrick Swayze, Katharine Ross
summary: Writer-director Richard Kelly's trippy, mind-bending feature debut stars Jake Gyllenhaal as a troubled Midwestern teenager plagued by incessant sleepwalking, family drama and visions of a menacing 6-foot-tall, doomsday-prophesying rabbit.

title: Crimson Tide
cast: Gene Hackman, Denzel Washington, James Gandolfini, George Dzundza, Matt Craven, Viggo Mortensen
summary: Controversy boils over when Soviet rebels point weapons at the United States, and the tactical message for one nuclear sub is cut off in transmission.

title: Into the Wild
cast: Emile Hirsch, Marcia Gay Harden, William Hurt, Jena Malone, Brian Dierker, Catherine Keener, Vince Vaughn, Hal Holbrook, Kristen Stewart, Zach Galifianakis
summary: A young man gives up everything -- including his trust fund and ties to a seemingly stable family -- to lead a solitary life in the wild, eschewing convention to trek across Alaska's harsh and unforgiving terrain.

title: In Our Nature
cast: Zach Gilford, Jena Malone, John Slattery, Gabrielle Union, David Ilku, Lisa Velten, Lola Cook, Hudson Price
summary: Seth and Andie had the perfect weekend getaway planned, until a booking error put Seth's estranged father and his girlfriend in the same condo. The four agree to make the best of the unexpected arrangement, with unexpected consequences for all.

title: For Ellen
cast: Paul Dano, Jon Heder, Shaylena Mandigo, Jena Malone, Margarita Levieva, Dakota Johnson, Alex Mauriello
summary: Would-be rock star Joby is forced to duel for joint custody of his 6-year-old daughter, Ellen, when his wife decides to end their marriage. Long absent from his daughter's life, he must now convince the court that he deserves to share in her future.

title: The Messenger

summary: An injured soldier is paired with a by-the-book captain to notify families of their loss -- a job that bonds them as they debate differing views on serving America. At odds at first, the two find common ground while facing life's variety of battles.

summary: When his horoscope forecasts a five-star day full of perfection and possibility, Jake Gibson is more than a little miffed when he finds himself on the wrong end of everything, from getting fired to being cheated on by his girlfriend.

title: The Ballad of Lucy Whipple

summary: When recently widowed Arvella Whipple pulls up stakes and moves her family from New England to a California gold-rush town, her teenage daughter hates their new home. But with time, she learns to appreciate her frontier environment.

title: Teenage
cast: Jena Malone, Ben Whishaw, Julia Hummer, Jessie Usher
summary: Filmmaker Matt Wolf explores the origins of the modern-day "teenager" -- a demographic that didn't even exist until the mid-20th century.

title: The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
cast: Jennifer Lawrence, Josh Hutcherson, Liam Hemsworth, Elizabeth Banks, Woody Harrelson, Lenny Kravitz, Philip Seymour Hoffman, Jeffrey Wright, Toby Jones, Willow Shields, Sam Claflin, Lynn Cohen, Jena Malone, Amanda Plummer, Alan Ritchson, Stanley Tucci, Don
summary: After her triumph in the Hunger Games, Katniss Everdeen travels through the districts on a "Victor's Tour" while a rebellion gathers steam around her.

title: Night Train to Lisbon
cast: Jeremy Irons, Mélanie Laurent, Jack Huston, Martina Gedeck, Tom Courtenay, August Diehl, Bruno Ganz, Lena Olin, Christopher Lee, Charlotte Rampling
summary: A Swiss professor seeks to uncover the truth about the life and death of a Portuguese poet who was dedicated to overthrowing Salazar's dictatorship.

title: The Ninth Gate
cast: Johnny Depp, Frank Langella, Lena Olin, Emmanuelle Seigner, Barbara Jefford, Jack Taylor, José López Rodero, Tony Amoni, James Russo, Willy Holt
summary: An international search for a rare copy of a demonic tome, "The Nine Gates of the Shadow Kingdom," brings an unscrupulous book dealer deep into a world of murder, double-dealing and Satanic worship in director Roman Polanski's gothic mystery.

title: The Night and the Moment
cast: Willem Dafoe, Lena Olin, Miranda Richardson, Jean-Claude Carriere, Carole Richert, Ivan Bacciocchi, Christine Sireyzol, Guy Verame
summary: A philandering writer (Willem Dafoe) in search of true love accepts an invitation from an aristocratic salonniere (Lena Olin), only to insinuate himself into her house and try to seduce her with stories of his various conquests. But what he doesn't realize is that their passions date back to his recent imprisonment, when she was incarcerated in the cell beside his.

title: Hollywood Homicide
cast: Harrison Ford, Josh Hartnett, Lena Olin, Bruce Greenwood, Isaiah Washington, Lolita Davidovich, Keith David, Master P, Gladys Knight, Lou Diamond Phillips
summary: When a rap group is killed onstage, lawman Joe Gavilan and his partner, K.C. Calden -- two cops with ambitions beyond police work -- must focus on solving the crime. But before long, their moonlighting becomes a distraction.

title: Darkness
cast: Anna Paquin, Lena Olin, Iain Glen, Giancarlo Giannini, Fele Martínez, Stephan Enquist, Fermin Reixach, Francesc Pages, Craig Stevenson, Paula Fernandez
summary: Regina and her parents have moved into a house in the country, but the home's dark past begins to haunt them and the entire family is put into peril.

title: Ordinary Decent Criminal
cast: Kevin Spacey, Linda Fiorentino, Peter Mullan, Stephen Dillane, Helen Baxendale, David Hayman, Patrick Malahide, Gerard McSorley, David Kelly, Gary Lydon
summary: In this taut crime thriller, a charming thief delights in plotting heists with the kind of élan that makes him popular in the very city he plunders.

title: See No Evil, Hear No Evil
cast: Richard Pryor, Gene Wilder, Joan Severance, Kevin Spacey, Alan North, Anthony Zerbe, Louis Giambalvo, Kirsten Childs
summary: Wally is blind, and Dave is deaf. But when a man is murdered outside the newsstand where they work, the police collar the unlikely duo.

title: Proof
cast: Gwyneth Paltrow, Anthony Hopkins, Jake Gyllenhaal, Danny McCarthy, Hope Davis, Tobiasz Daszkiewicz, Gary Houston, Anne Wittman, Leigh Zimmerman, Colin Stinton
summary: A devoted daughter must face her fears as she comes to terms with the death of her father, a brilliant mathematician crippled by mental instability.

title: Edison Force
cast: Morgan Freeman, Kevin Spacey, Justin Timberlake, LL Cool J, Dylan McDermott, John Heard, Cary Elwes, Roselyn Sanchez, Piper Perabo
summary: Justin Timberlake, in his feature-film debut, stars as a reporter fresh from journalism school who uncovers a hot story of lies and deception within the Edison police department, and does everything in his power to unravel it.

title: The Usual Suspects
cast: Kevin Spacey, Gabriel Byrne, Stephen Baldwin, Kevin Pollak, Chazz Palminteri, Benicio Del Toro, Pete Postlethwaite, Suzy Amis, Giancarlo Esposito, Dan Hedaya
summary: When five unacquainted crooks are hauled into a police station to appear in a criminal lineup, they decide to pull off a heist together. The plan gets complicated, however, when they intermix with an underworld kingpin named Keyser Söze.

title: Swimming with Sharks
cast: Frank Whaley, Kevin Spacey, Michelle Forbes, Benicio Del Toro, T.E. Russell, Roy Dotrice, Matthew Flint, Patrick Fischler, Jerry Levine
summary: Naive Guy lands a job as assistant to Buddy Ackerman, a repulsive studio exec who turns Guy's daily routine into a pride-swallowing siege. Guy is eager to climb the ladder of success, but Buddy stops at nothing to grab credit and foil Guy's plans.

title: Inseparable
cast: Kevin Spacey, Daniel Wu, Beibi Gong, Ni Yan, Peter Stormare, Kenneth Tsang, Mo Zhang, Tongsheng Han
summary: Plagued by personal tragedies and troubles at work, Li is on the brink of ending it all until his expat neighbor gives him a new lease on life. Forging an unlikely bond, the two men don superhero costumes and anoint themselves crime fighters.

summary: Jack Lemmon, Al Pacino, Ed Harris and Alan Arkin chew the words of David Mamet's script (based on his own stage play) as a group of Chicago real estate salesmen vying for the best "leads" at a small firm that sells property in resort areas.

title: Casino Jack
cast: Kevin Spacey, Barry Pepper, Kelly Preston, Jon Lovitz, Rachelle Lefevre, Ruth Marshall, Graham Greene, Hannah Endicott-Douglas, John Robinson, Jason Weinberg
summary: No stranger to wealth and power, slick lobbyist Jack Abramoff lands deep in a political corruption scandal after bilking millions from Indian tribes. Greed and vanity catch up to the charismatic Abramoff in the form of the mob, the media and the law.

title: House of Cards: Season 1 (Recap)
cast: Kevin Spacey, Robin Wright, Kate Mara, Corey Stoll, Michael Kelly, Sakina Jaffrey, Kristen Connolly, Constance Zimmer, Sebastian Arcelus, Nathan Darrow
summary: Enraged when the newly-elected president publicly betrays him, veteran Congressman Frank Underwood makes a secret pledge to exact revenge and seize the reins of power through a complex plot of manipulation, deceit and corruption.

title: House of Cards: Season 1 with Bonus Commentary
cast: Kevin Spacey, Robin Wright, Kate Mara, Corey Stoll, Michael Kelly, Sakina Jaffrey, Kristen Connolly, Constance Zimmer, Sebastian Arcelus, Nathan Darrow
summary: Watch the first season of this Emmy-winning series all over again, this time with scene-by-scene audio commentary from directors including David Fincher and Joel Schumacher, who provide a behind-the-camera analysis for each episode.

title: American Masters: Johnny Carson: King of Late Night
cast: Kevin Spacey, Johnny Carson, Steve Allen, Jay Leno, Jimmy Fallon, David Letterman, Conan O'Brien
summary: As host of "The Tonight Show" for 30 years, Johnny Carson was seen by more people on more occasions than anyone else in American history. Explore Carson's life and career, as well as the history of his beloved television program.

title: House of Cards
cast: Kevin Spacey, Robin Wright, Kate Mara, Corey Stoll, Michael Kelly, Sakina Jaffrey, Kristen Connolly, Constance Zimmer, Sebastian Arcelus, Nathan Darrow
summary: Ruthless Congressman Francis Underwood and his ambitious wife Claire will stop at nothing to conquer Washington D.C. in this dark political drama, winner of three Emmy Awards, including Best Director, and a Golden Globe for Best Actress. Season 2 begins February 14.

title: American Beauty
cast: Kevin Spacey, Annette Bening, Thora Birch, Wes Bentley, Mena Suvari, Chris Cooper, Peter Gallagher, Allison Janney, Scott Bakula, Sam Robards, Ara Celi, John Cho, Sue Casey, Amber Smith, Matthew Kimbrough
summary: While struggling to endure his tightly wound wife, an unfulfilling job and a surly teen, a man becomes obsessed with one of his daughter's friends.

title: The Ref

summary: Gus, a burglar, is about to score on Christmas Eve by breaking into a posh home in the suburbs. But his plans change when he trips up the alarm and takes the occupants hostage. Or is it the other way around?

title: Now: In the Wings on a World Stage
cast: Kevin Spacey, Maureen Anderman, Stephen Lee Anderson, Jeremy Bobb, Nathan Darrow, Jack Ellis, Annabel Scholey, Gavin Stenhouse, Hannah Stokely, Sam Mendes, Gary Powell, Chukwudi Iwuji, Isaiah Johnson, Gemma Jones
summary: Go behind the scenes with leading man Kevin Spacey, director Sam Mendes and their collaborators on the Bridge Project's production of "Richard III."

title: Prozac Nation
cast: Christina Ricci, Jessica Lange, Jonathan Rhys Meyers, Jason Biggs, Anne Heche, Michelle Williams
summary: This adaptation of Elizabeth Wurtzel's memoir stars Christina Ricci as a girl on the verge of losing her grip on life after she leaves her emotionally unstable home for college. Her psychiatrist prescribes Prozac ... but is that her only choice?

title: But I'm a Cheerleader
cast: Natasha Lyonne, Clea DuVall, RuPaul, Bud Cort, Michelle Williams, Melanie Lynskey, Mink Stole, Cathy Moriarty, Robert Pine
summary: A "normal" teen cheerleader dating the football captain draws suspicion from parents and friends who think she's gay. Shipped off to a camp designed to shove her back in the closet, she meets a tomboy who helps her recognize her sexual orientation.

title: Take This Waltz
cast: Michelle Williams, Seth Rogen, Luke Kirby, Sarah Silverman, Jennifer Podemski, Diane D'Aquila, Vanessa Coelho, Graham Abbey

title: What My Husband Doesn't Know
cast: Bryan White, Michelle Williams, Ann Nesby, Clifton Davis, Tiffany Haddish, Diondre Jones, Esau McGraw, Chloe Spencer
summary: All the money and material things her successful husband provides don't make up for the emptiness Lena feels from his frequent absences -- and she soon finds herself tempted by a good-looking young handyman working in her home.

summary: This thought-provoking nighttime soap about a group of close-knit teens, led by dreamer Dawson Leery, frankly portrays the issues of adolescence that obsess young adults as they navigate through high school and college -- including sex, sex and sex.

summary: An American journalist, Zoe (played by the multitalented Daphna Kastner, who also wrote and directed the film), knows better than to go into a story with her mind already made up. But that's exactly what she does when she heads off to Spain to write about its men and their macho take (as she sees it) on relationships. As she tries to prove her thesis, she soon realizes that she doesn't know as much about the male sex as she thought.

title: Duress

The widower's troubles multiply when Abner forces him to become his criminal protege by threatening to execute Richard's daughter (Ariel Winter). In order to keep her alive, Richard must behave like his psychotic captor in this tautly suspenseful thriller.

title: Silent Hill: Revelation
cast: Adelaide Clemens, Kit Harington, Carrie-Anne Moss, Sean Bean, Radha Mitchell, Malcolm McDowell, Martin Donovan, Deborah Kara Unger
summary: Haunted by shocking nightmares and unsettled by her father's disappearance just before her 18th birthday, Heather goes on the hunt for him -- and discovers a disturbing truth about her own identity in this suspenseful sequel to the hit horror flick.

title: Pipe Dream

summary: After having a one-night-stand with an aspiring screenwriter, a New York City plumber, frustrated about the way his vocation is perceived by women, steals the writer's script and poses as a director to improve his chances in the dating arena.

title: Collaborator

summary: After critics savage his latest Broadway play, writer Robert Longfellow heads home to Los Angeles to care for his mother and work on schlocky movies. But when he runs into an old neighbor, his life takes a terrifying Hollywood-style plot turn.

title: Boss

summary: Kelsey Grammer stars in this dark drama as Chicago mayor Tom Kane, a viperous politician unafraid to step outside the law when it suits his interests.

title: Sabotage

title: Insomnia

summary: A woman and her daughter are caught in a game of cat-and-mouse with three burglars in their New York City home and are forced to retreat inside a vault. As the intruders try to breach the room's security, the embattled duo must stay one step ahead.

title: The Human Stain
cast: Nicole Kidman, Anthony Hopkins, Ed Harris, Gary Sinise, Mili Avital, Harry Lennix, Anna Deavere Smith, Kerry Washington, Ron Canada, John Finn
summary: A university classics professor becomes involved in a passionate relationship with a poor cleaning woman who's married to a jealous, violent man.

title: Our Song

summary: Experiencing growing pains while they're on summer vacation, three inner-city teenage girls with hectic schedules make life-changing decisions in this engrossing drama that encapsulates the untold difficulties of urban living.

title: The Details

summary: After discovering that his lawn has been completely destroyed by raccoons, frustrated Jeff foolishly cheats on his wife, Nealy, which leads to a series of agonizing predicaments involving his best friend's husband and next-door neighbor.

Marcus befriends Pat's young daughter and attempts to conquer his demons. Interfering with Marcus's good intentions are the neighborhood's continuing racial and social conflicts, as well as old enemies and friends -- both with scores to settle.

title: Scandal
cast: Kerry Washington, Columbus Short, Darby Stanchfield, Katie Lowes, Guillermo Díaz, Joshua Malina, Jeff Perry, Bellamy Young, Tony Goldwyn
summary: Olivia Pope leads a team of Washington, D.C., lawyers who specialize in making scandals disappear. As they secretly handle crises at the highest levels of government, the dysfunctional team must also cope with problems closer to home.

summary: A man is so eager to become a dad that he'll believe anything, including the notion that a baby-faced thief on the lam is really an abandoned toddler.

title: Jamesy Boy
cast: Mary-Louise Parker, Taissa Farmiga, James Woods, Ving Rhames, Spencer Lofranco, Rosa Salazar, Taboo, Ben Rosenfield, Michael Trotter
summary: An angry teen winds up in prison for running drugs and guns -- but his friendship with a killer gives him a chance to change his life for the better.

title: Diggstown
cast: James Woods, Heather Graham, Louis Gossett Jr., Bruce Dern, Oliver Platt, Randall Tex Cobb, Thomas Wilson Brown
summary: When two swindlers involve an aging boxer in a plan to dupe a rich Diggstown resident, the fighter first makes the con men earn their stripes.

title: Riding in Cars with Boys

summary: After sleeping with a boy she barely knew, Beverly gets married on a whim and discovers that her newborn isn't the only one who has a lot of growing up to do. Her teenage husband is a still a kid -- and so is she.

title: The Hard Way
cast: Michael J. Fox, James Woods, Stephen Lang, Annabella Sciorra, Penny Marshall
summary: An actor needs to get under a cop's skin to research an upcoming role, and he picks an irritable New York City hard case as his source material. As if dealing with the pesky thespian weren't enough, the cop has a serial killer to catch.

title: Scary Movie 2

summary: While the original parodied slasher flicks like Scream, Keenen Ivory Wayans' sequel to Scary Movie takes comedic aim at haunted house movies. A group of students visits a mansion called Hell House, and murderous high jinks ensue.

title: The Virgin Suicides

summary: Ronald and Sara Lisbon are raising five alluring, adolescent daughters on a short leash in 1970s suburbia. When the youngest, Cecilia, kills herself, Sara attempts to shelter the rest of them from intrigued neighborhood boys.

title: Another Day in Paradise

title: Hercules
cast: Tate Donovan, Danny DeVito, James Woods, Susan Egan, Bobcat Goldthwait, Matt Frewer, Rip Torn, Samantha Eggar, Barbara Barrie, Hal Holbrook
summary: In Disney's animated take on Greek mythology, the heavenly Hercules is stripped of his immortality and raised on Earth instead of Olympus, where he's forced to take on Hades and assorted monsters.

summary: Respected Army Gen. Joe Campbell is headed for a hero's retirement -- until his daughter is raped and murdered on his military base, and warrant officers and ex-lovers Paul Brenner and Sara Sunhill are given 36 hours to solve the convoluted case.

title: The Onion Field

summary: This true story follows the psychological collapse of cop Karl, whose partner is murdered in front of him. Karl tries to put his life back together while wrestling with the guilt of surviving the ordeal and letting the killers get away.

When the boy's abilities are recognized, Jonah's world opens as he learns sign language. Jonah's struggles to make himself understood provide an affecting, heart-rending family drama with an important message.

title: The Choirboys

But when a joke goes too far and an innocent man gets caught in the crossfire, the cops close ranks and try to cover up the incident. Charles Durning, James Woods, Randy Quaid and Louis Gossett Jr. star in this dark comedy.

title: Coma
cast: Lauren Ambrose, Steven Pasquale, Geena Davis, Ellen Burstyn, James Woods, Richard Dreyfuss, James Rebhorn, Joe Morton, Michael Weston, Joseph Mazzello
summary: In this made-for-cable miniseries based on Robin Cook's bestselling novel, a doctor begins to suspect that something is amiss when several seemingly healthy patients begin lapsing into comas after routine operations.

title: Stuart Little 2

summary: Zany misadventures are in store as lovable city mouse Stuart and his human brother, George, raise the roof in this sequel to the 1999 blockbuster.

Based on David Rabe's award-winning Broadway play, the film co-stars George Dzundza and Guy Boyd as the recruits' jaded sergeants.

title: A Cat in Paris

summary: In this Oscar-nominated animated feature, little Zoe discovers that her cat, Dino, moonlights as the companion to Nico, a burglar with a heart of gold. Soon Zoe is  drawn into a thriller filled with gangsters, jewels and the rooftops of Paris.

title: Family Weekend

summary: After her preoccupied parents fail to attend her jump-rope competition, 16-year-old Emily Smith-Dungy decides to hold them hostage until they change their attitude. But her plan hits a snag when the police step in.

title: Girl in Progress

summary: While single mom Grace is distracted by her own work, life and romantic issues, her teen daughter, Ansiedad, adopts her own plan for growing up. Patricia Arquette stars as the English teacher who inspires Ansiedad to declare her early freedom.

title: Category 8
cast: Matthew Modine, Maxim Roy, Ted Whittall, Trevor Hayes, Kate Drummond, Kalinka Petrie, Spiro Malandrakis, Alain Goulem, Susan Hogan, Francis X. McCarthy
summary: When a government experiment to harness the sun's power goes horribly awry and sends a massive fireball hurtling toward Earth, it's up to a renegade scientist to save the planet by reversing the cataclysm -- against seemingly impossible odds.

title: Revenge

summary: In this saga of illicit love, a former fighter pilot is attracted to the sultry wife of his powerful Mexican host (whose name means shark in Spanish).

title: Silverado

summary: Two brothers, ex-prisoner Emmett (Scott Glenn) and current prisoner Jake (Kevin Costner), team up with a butcher named Mal (Danny Glover) and Paden (Kevin Kline), a man left to die in the desert by outlaws, to take on the crooked sheriff (Brian Dennehy) of Silverado. Their families, who all live in the New Mexico town, depend on their heroics. Jeff Goldblum co-stars in director Lawrence Kasdan's classic Western with an Oscar-nominated score.

title: Bull Durham
cast: Kevin Costner, Susan Sarandon, Tim Robbins, Trey Wilson, Robert Wuhl, William O'Leary, David Neidorf, Danny Gans, Tom Silardi, Rick Marzan
summary: The perennially pitiful Durham Bulls ink pitching phenom "Nuke" LaLoosh (Tim Robbins), a gifted but undisciplined rookie, in hopes that he'll usher the team to victory. But it's up to seasoned bush-league catcher "Crash" Davis (Kevin Costner) to keep him in line. Meanwhile, a winsome groupie (Susan Sarandon) who confers sexual favors on a new player each season chooses Nuke as this year's beneficiary. The problem is, she's more attracted to Crash.

title: The Company Men
cast: Ben Affleck, Kevin Costner, Tommy Lee Jones, Chris Cooper, Craig T. Nelson, Maria Bello, Rosemarie DeWitt, John Doman, Tonye Patano, Cady Huffman
summary: Written, directed and produced by John Wells, this indie drama stars Ben Affleck as a successful businessman who comes face-to-face with America's downsizing epidemic when he loses his job and is forced to take a construction gig.

title: 3 Days to Kill

summary: A terminally ill secret agent accepts a risky mission in exchange for an experimental drug that might save him -- if he can survive its side effects.

title: Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit
cast: Chris Pine, Kevin Costner, Kenneth Branagh, Keira Knightley
summary: CIA analyst Jack Ryan tries to thwart a terrorist plot to bring down the U.S. economy in this action-thriller starring Chris Pine in the title role.

Bernard learns of a British drug that's  effective but hasn't been approved in the U.S. yet, and he resolves to help Felice even if it means breaking the law.

title: JFK: A President Betrayed

summary: When TV reporter Bruce Nolan angrily ridicules God, the Almighty responds by giving Bruce all His divine powers. But can Bruce improve on perfection?

summary: With a massive comet threatening to destroy Earth, the U.S. president appoints a steely veteran astronaut to lead a crew into space to destroy it.

title: Bram Stoker's Dracula

Leonard, however, is certain Maria's intentions are pure ... but are they?

summary: Academy Award-winning director Robert Zemeckis brings the legendary Old English epic of &NFi;Beowulf&NFi_; to life in this deftly animated tale of a Scandinavian hero who's known for slaying dragons.

summary: Based on Mike Mignola's cult comic book series, this fast-paced live-action film tells the dark story of Hellboy, a charismatic demon who's put on Earth by the Nazis to terrorize the rest of the world. But Hellboy has other plans. Deciding to fight for good instead of evil, he vows to rid the world of supernatural monsters and the powers that rule them.

title: Bunraku

title: A Stoning in Fulham County

title: Beauty and the Beast

The two share a deep bond as they explore the chambers, tunnels and secrets of a magical underground world where a Utopian community of outcasts thrives.

summary: A high school dropout and his friends start smuggling huge amounts of pot across the Canadian border, but the consequences are heavier than expected.

summary: Just as rowdy alien Stitch begins settling in with his new adopted family, he suddenly goes haywire: It seems his molecular structure is off-kilter, restoring his destructive behavior. Can plucky island girl Lilo find a way to set things right?

title: The Motel Life
cast: Emile Hirsch, Stephen Dorff, Dakota Fanning, Kris Kristofferson, Joshua Leonard, Noah Harpster, Garrett Backstrom, Andrew Lee, Nancy Youngblut, Jenica Bergere
summary: In this affecting indie drama, two luckless but inseparable brothers take it on the lam after one of them is involved in a fatal hit-and-run accident.

title: Hook

title: Confessions of a Dangerous Mind

title: Mystic Pizza

title: Khumba

title: Parting Glances

summary: Upwardly mobile Robert accepts a long-term assignment in Africa that will inevitably strain his relationship with his lover, Michael.

title: Desperado

title: 28 Days

summary: After her drunken antics ruin her sister's wedding and result in major property damage, journalist Gwen Cummings enters rehab, where she runs afoul of the program director -- and soon meets a fellow resident who changes her outlook.

title: Airheads

summary: The Lone Rangers have heavy-metal aspirations and a single demo tape that they can't get anyone to play. The solution: Hijack a radio station and hold the deejays hostage until they agree to broadcast the band's tape.

title: Tales from the Darkside: The Movie
cast: Deborah Harry, Matthew Lawrence, Christian Slater, Steve Buscemi, Donald Van Horn, Julianne Moore, James Remar, Rae Dawn Chong, Robert Klein, David Johansen

title: Spy Kids 2: The Island of Lost Dreams

summary: Kurt Russell reprises his role as antihero Snake Plissken. This time, a cataclysmic temblor hits Los Angeles, turning it into an island. The president (Cliff Robertson) views the quake as a sign from above, expels Los Angeles from the country and makes it a penal colony for those found guilty of moral crimes. When his daughter, part of a resistance movement, steals the control unit for a doomsday weapon, Snake again gets tapped to save the day.

In fact, the entire world has been thrown out of balance, and they're there seeking the Chosen One -- the one soul who can set the universe right. With no better plan, Paul begins keeping an eye out for his moment of destiny.

title: Glick Doesn't Do Red Carpet: Jiminy Glick at the Independent Spirit Awards
cast: Martin Short, Rainn Wilson, Dennis Hopper, Maria Bello, Ellen Page, Steve Buscemi, Ivan Reitman, Jason Reitman, John Waters, Allison Janney

He gets couch time with host Rainn Wilson, Maria Bello, Ellen Page, Dennis Hopper, Steve Buscemi, Ed Begley Jr. and more, who take Glick's insults all in stride. Plenty of pillow fighting, donut munching and inappropriateness abound.

title: Graham Chapman: Anatomy of a Liar
cast: Graham Chapman, John Cleese, Terry Gilliam, Terry Jones, Michael Palin
director: Bill Jones, Jeff Simpson, Benjamin Timlett

title: The Original Kings of Comedy

title: DreamWorks Happy Holidays from Madagascar

title: All's Faire in Love

title: Barbershop

summary: A $50,000 reward offer for information about a recent heist sends a barbershop on Chicago's south side, already a hub of rumors, into a frenzy.

summary: When a glitzy, high-class hair salon opens across the street, barbershop owner Calvin finds his mom-and-pop business threatened in this comic sequel.

title: A Haunted House 2
cast: Marlon Wayans, Jaime Pressly, Essence Atkins, Gabriel Iglesias, Cedric the Entertainer, Missi Pyle, Ashley Rickards, Affion Crockett, Steele Stebbins, Rick Overton, Hayes MacArthur, Dave Sheridan
summary: Marlon Wayans returns in this spoofy sequel as the grieving Malcolm, who's trying to move on after his girlfriend's untimely tragic death.

title: The Fox and the Hound 2

summary: In Disney's animated follow-up to the 1981 classic, Tod the fox and Copper the hound see their friendship put to the test when Copper finds fame with a howling country-and-western dog band -- and jealousy strikes Tod.

title: Sneakers

title: Incident at Oglala: The Leonard Peltier Story

Featuring reenactments and interviews with key players in the incident, the film offers evidence that the government's prosecution of Peltier was unjust and politically motivated.

title: The Great Gatsby

title: Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid

title: Indecent Proposal

summary: For one million dollars, a handsome billionaire proposes to Diana that they spend a single night together. Her husband is a cash-strapped architect who could use the cash. Will she do it?

title: The Great Waldo Pepper

As the jaded public demands increasingly risky tricks, Waldo and Kessler both leave barnstorming behind and head to Hollywood to film a high-flying war flick.

title: Buck

The master horseman reveals details of his troubled childhood and his dawning awareness of new ways that humans and horses might work with one another. As Buck learns more about horses, he finds that the ways we communicate with our animal companions offer lessons on how we relate to fellow human beings.

The documentary includes commentary from Robert Redford, Kris Kristofferson, Sam Shepard, Val Kilmer, Jackson Browne, Bonnie Raitt, Amy Ray of the Indigo Girls and Wilma Mankiller, the first woman principal chief of the Cherokee Nation.

title: This Property Is Condemned

summary: When railroad official Owen Legate visits a small Depression-era town to shut down its rail yard, he begins a passionate affair with a local girl.

title: All Is Lost
cast: Robert Redford
summary: In this harrowing drama -- which has no dialogue -- a man stranded alone at sea courageously battles a ferocious storm as he struggles to survive.

title: Serial Killing 101
cast: Thomas Haden Church, Justin Urich, Lisa Loeb, Rick Overton, George Murdock, Barbara Niven, Stuart Stone, Raymond O'Connor
