title: Another Happy Day
cast: Ellen Barkin, Ezra Miller, Ellen Burstyn, Demi Moore, Thomas Haden Church, Kate Bosworth, George Kennedy, Jeffrey DeMunn, Siobhan Fallon, Diana Scarwid
summary: Upper-crust family dysfunction takes center stage in this drama, which stars Ellen Barkin as a divorcée attending the highbrow wedding of the son she barely knows and trying to hold her own against a family that couches judgment in every smile.

title: Whitewash
cast: Thomas Haden Church, Marc Labrèche, Emanuel Hoss-Desmarais, Vincent Hoss-Desmarais, Geneviève Laroche, Isabelle Nélisse, Anie Pascale
summary: After recklessly killing a pedestrian, a drunken snowplow operator finds himself stranded in the forest -- and courting death in the bitter cold.

title: Mr. Smith Goes to Washington
cast: James Stewart, Jean Arthur, Claude Rains, Edward Arnold, Guy Kibbee, Thomas Mitchell, Eugene Pallette, Beulah Bondi, H.B. Warner, Harry Carey Sr.
summary: In Frank Capra's classic, junior senator Jefferson Smith remains idealistic despite widespread corruption among his cynical colleagues in Washington.

title: The Clairvoyant
cast: Claude Rains, Fay Wray, Ben Field, Jane Baxter, Athole Stewart, Mary Clare
summary: Performing his music hall mind-reading act, Maximus (Claude Rains) suddenly experiences real precognition and discovers his talent is mysteriously triggered in the company of a lovely woman, Christine (Jane Baxter), whose presence also infuriates his jealous wife, Rene (Fay Wray). Along with his accurate premonitions come fame and fortune. But suspicions are raised, and a foretold disaster puts the seer in the hot seat.

title: The Passionate Friends
cast: Ann Todd, Claude Rains, Trevor Howard, Isabel Dean, Betty Ann Davies, Arthur Howard, Guido Lorraine
summary: While staying in the Swiss Alps, Mary finds herself torn between the convenience and financial comfort of her marriage to Claude, who is much older than her, and the passion of her old flame, Steven.

title: Caesar and Cleopatra
cast: Claude Rains, Vivien Leigh, Stewart Granger, Flora Robson, Francis L. Sullivan, Basil Sydney, Cecil Parker, Raymond Lovell, Anthony Eustrel, Ernest Thesiger
summary: In this Oscar-nominated film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's play, the aging Caesar (Claude Rains) comes to Alexandria to tutor young Cleopatra (Vivien Leigh) in the ways of rule, allowing her to wrestle the throne away from her brother, Ptolemy. But as time progresses, Caesar's feelings for Cleopatra turn romantic and he vows to marry her. Stewart Granger co-stars in this epic drama directed by Gabriel Pascal.

title: The Bells of St. Mary's
cast: Bing Crosby, Ingrid Bergman, Henry Travers, William Gargan, Ruth Donnelly, Joan Carroll, Martha Sleeper, Una O'Connor, Rhys Williams
summary: Good-natured Father O'Malley is sent to help the struggling St. Mary's Academy, where his leadership style irritates strong-willed Sister Benedict.

title: Barbarella
cast: Jane Fonda, John Phillip Law, Anita Pallenberg, Milo O'Shea, Marcel Marceau, Claude Dauphin, Véronique Vendell, Giancarlo Cobelli, David Hemmings, Ugo Tognazzi
summary: A shapely 41st-century space traveler must apprehend scientist Durand Durand, whose creation threatens to bring evil back to the galaxy. En route, Barbarella discovers the joys of celestial sex and has kinky misadventures with bizarre characters.

title: All Together
cast: Guy Bedos, Daniel Brühl, Geraldine Chaplin, Jane Fonda, Claude Rich, Pierre Richard, Bernard Malaka, Camino Texeira
summary: Instead of living in a retirement home, five aging friends decide to move in together after one of them suffers a heart attack. The two couples and one widower are joined by a young caregiver, an ethnology student who is studying the group.

title: TEDTalks: For All of Womankind
cast: Isabel Allende, Sheryl Sandberg, Eve Ensler, Jane Fonda, Sarah Kay, Tony Porter, Courtney Martin, Sheryl WuDunn, Kavita Ramdas, Nadia Al-Sakkaf
summary: Celebrate extraordinary women of our time, who are conquering the world with their drive, wit, intelligence and grace. Former U.S. Secretary of State Madeline Albright, actress Jane Fonda and author Arianna Huffington are among the presenters.

title: On Golden Pond
cast: Katharine Hepburn, Henry Fonda, Jane Fonda, Doug McKeon, Dabney Coleman, William Lanteau, Christopher Rydell
summary: A retired professor and his wife go on an annual trip to their summer vacation home. But a teen left in their care disrupts the couple's tranquility.

title: Peace, Love & Misunderstanding
cast: Jane Fonda, Catherine Keener, Jeffrey Dean Morgan, Chace Crawford, Elizabeth Olsen, Nat Wolff, Marissa O'Donnell, Rosanna Arquette, Kyle MacLachlan, Katharine McPhee
summary: A conservative lawyer recovering from a domestic crisis reconnects with her free-spirited mother, and finds both peace and romance along the way.

title: Better Living Through Chemistry
cast: Sam Rockwell, Olivia Wilde, Michelle Monaghan, Ray Liotta, Jane Fonda, Ben Schwartz, Ken Howard, Norbert Leo Butz
summary: When an unhappily married small-town pharmacist hooks up with a hot customer, he's soon caught up in a web of sex, drugs and potential murder.

title: Unfinished Song
cast: Terence Stamp, Gemma Arterton, Christopher Eccleston, Vanessa Redgrave, Anne Reid, Elizabeth Counsell, Ram John Holder, Bill Thomas, Orla Hill
summary: With his wife Marion terminally ill, 72-year-old Arthur sees a future that's nothing but grim. But when he takes Marion's place in their church's very unconventional choir, he begins to find joy in life again.

title: A Month by the Lake
cast: Vanessa Redgrave, Edward Fox, Uma Thurman, Alida Valli, Carlo Cartier, Alessandro Gassman, Natalia Bizzi, Paolo Lombardi
summary: While vacationing on Lake Como in pre-World War II Italy, a middle-aged English woman develops an interest in a fellow guest, a stuffy major in the British army. Before she can make her move, the arrival of a young nanny complicates her plans.

title: Shades of Fear
cast: Vanessa Redgrave, John Hurt, Jonathan Pryce, Dorothy Tutin, Rakie Ayola, Carmen Munroe, Oliver Samuels, David Harewood
summary: Mystery lurks in the shadowy corners of a luxurious ocean liner as a young woman traveling on her own enters into a romantic liaison with a handsome stranger who may be an accomplished art forger and a cold-hearted killer. Vanessa Redgrave, John Hurt and Jonathan Pryce star.

title: Mother's Boys
cast: Jamie Lee Curtis, Peter Gallagher, Joanne Whalley, Vanessa Redgrave, Luke Edwards, Colin Ward, Joey Zimmerman, Joss Ackland, Paul Guilfoyle, J.E. Freeman
summary: After abandoning her family, Jude Madigan abruptly returns home three years later to discover another woman has taken her place. Obsessed with reclaiming her former life, Jude will let nothing stand in her way.

title: How About You
cast: Joss Ackland, Hayley Atwell, Orla Brady, Brenda Fricker, Elizabeth Moynihan, Joan O'Hara, Vanessa Redgrave, Imelda Staunton
summary: When the manager of a retirement home in the Irish countryside asks her younger sister, Ellie (Hayley Atwell), to run the facility during the holidays, four mischievous residents take advantage of the power vacuum and turn the place upside down. As Ellie learns to take charge, the residents also come to terms with their own troubles. Anthony Byrne directs this heartwarming comedy-drama co-starring Joss Ackland and Vanessa Redgrave.

title: Coriolanus
cast: Ralph Fiennes, Gerard Butler, Brian Cox, Vanessa Redgrave, Jessica Chastain, James Nesbitt, Paul Jesson, Lubna Azabal, Ashraf Barhom, Dragan Mieanovie
summary: Actor Ralph Fiennes makes his directorial debut with this modern update of Shakespeare's tale about the arrogant general who is banished by the republic he protected at all costs, provoking him to align with former foes and wreak bloody revenge.

title: Animals United
cast: James Corden, Stephen Fry, Andy Serkis, Dawn French, Vanessa Redgrave, Jim Broadbent, Jason Donovan, Omid Djalili, Michael Glover
summary: When their water disappears, a group of animals in the African savannah sets out on an incredible journey to find a new source. Soon, they discover that humans are hoarding the water to use at a luxury resort.

title: Miral
cast: Hiam Abbass, Freida Pinto, Willem Dafoe, Vanessa Redgrave, Asma Al Shiukhy, Neemeh Khalil, Jamil Khoury, Basel Husseini, Yasmine Elmasri, Omar Metwally
summary: After rescuing children who survived a massacre in Jerusalem in 1948, a Palestinian woman establishes an orphanage that helps thousands of other children. But the success of her institution is tested when a pupil gets a taste of radical politics.

title: Call the Midwife
cast: Jessica Raine, Vanessa Redgrave, Jenny Agutter, Pam Ferris, Judy Parfitt, Miranda Hart
summary: Set in the 1950s, this period drama based on the memoirs of Jennifer Worth follows new midwife Jenny Lee and the other midwives and nuns working in a nursing convent in an impoverished section of London's East End.

title: Little Odessa
cast: Tim Roth, Edward Furlong, Moira Kelly, Vanessa Redgrave, Paul Guilfoyle, Natalya Andreychenko, Maximilian Schell, David Vadim
summary: Gun-for-hire Joshua Shapira, on assignment for the Russian mob, returns to his former Brighton Beach neighborhood where he mends fences with his brother and an ex-girlfriend. But Joshua's estranged dad wants nothing to do with his hoodlum son.

title: Mission: Impossible
cast: Tom Cruise, Jon Voight, Emmanuelle Béart, Henry Czerny, Jean Reno, Ving Rhames, Kristin Scott Thomas, Vanessa Redgrave, Dale Dye, Marcel Iures
summary: The leader of a crack espionage team whose perilous operation has gone awry discovers a mole has penetrated the CIA -- and he's the No. 1 suspect.

title: Once Upon a Time in the West
cast: Henry Fonda, Charles Bronson, Claudia Cardinale, Jason Robards, Gabriele Ferzetti, Paolo Stoppa, Woody Strode, Jack Elam, Keenan Wynn, Frank Wolff
summary: Directed by Sergio Leone, this classic spaghetti Western stars Henry Fonda as a sadistic gunslinger hired by a cutthroat railroad tycoon to kill anyone who stands in the way of his trans-American iron horse.

title: Tora! Tora! Tora!
cast: Martin Balsam, Soh Yamamura, Joseph Cotten, Tatsuya Mihashi, E.G. Marshall, James Whitmore, Takahiro Tamura, Eijirô Tôno, Jason Robards, Wesley Addy
director: Richard Fleischer, Kinji Fukasuka, Toshio Masuda
summary: Named for the Japanese phrase that signals the start of an attack, Tora! Tora! Tora! tells both the American and Japanese versions of the infamous attack on Pearl Harbor that catapulted the United States into World War II.

title: Murders in the Rue Morgue
cast: Jason Robards, Herbert Lom, Christine Kaufmann, Adolfo Celi, Maria Perschy, Michael Dunn, Lilli Palmer, Peter Arne
summary: In the midst of preparing his theater troupe for their upcoming production, Cesar (Jason Robards) struggles to soothe his wife, Madeleine (Christine Kaufmann), who's been suffering dreadful nightmares, and races to figure out who is brutally murdering his lead actors one by one. A loose adaptation of an Edgar Allan Poe story, this chilling horror tale effectively weaves back and forth between disturbing dreams and reality.

title: iSteve
cast: Justin Long, Jorge Garcia, James Urbaniak, Michaela Watkins, John Ross Bowie, Steve Tom
summary: Justin Long stars in this full-length Funny or Die parody as Apple Inc. icon Steve Jobs, the free-thinking visionary -- and onetime social outcast -- who ushered in a computing revolution.

title: Ken Burns: The West
cast: Peter Coyote, Philip Bosco, Jimmy Smits, Murphy Guyer, John Trudell, Eli Wallach, Jason Robards, Adam Arkin, Peter Gallagher, Arthur Miller
summary: Historian and Oscar nominee Ken Burns and his talented team mine vintage photographs, music, maps, letters, newspapers and more to bring to life the struggles and challenges Americans faced in the 19th century as they embarked on westward expansion.

title: Philadelphia
cast: Tom Hanks, Denzel Washington, Jason Robards, Mary Steenburgen, Antonio Banderas, Ron Vawter, Charles Napier, Joanne Woodward, Karen Finley, Buzz Kilman
summary: Philadelphia attorney Andrew Beckett launches a wrongful termination suit against his law firm when they fire him because he's gay and HIV-positive.

title: The Odessa File
cast: Jon Voight, Maximilian Schell, Maria Schell, Mary Tamm, Derek Jacobi, Peter Jeffrey, Klaus Lowitsch, Kurt Meisel
summary: In 1963, a freelance German reporter finds himself involved in the hunt for a former concentration camp commander who vanished after World War II.

title: House of the Sleeping Beauties
cast: Vadim Glowna, Angela Winkler, Maximilian Schell, Birol Ünel, Mona Glass, Benjamin Cabuk
summary: Edmond, a widower in his 60s, learns about a type of brothel in which men can pay to lie in bed next to a young, beautiful, sleeping woman. Edmond finds great solace in his visits, even as he discovers a shocking secret about the place.

title: Marlene
cast: Marlene Dietrich, Annie Albers, Bernard Haller, Maximilian Schell, Marta Rakosnik, Patricia Schell, Ivana Spinell, William von Stranz
summary: Actor-filmmaker Maximilian Schell crafts this Oscar-nominated portrait of reclusive German screen siren Marlene Dietrich, who allowed Schell to record her musings on her life and set them against a backdrop of film clips, stills and newsreel footage.

title: My Sister Maria
cast: Maria Schell, Maximilian Schell, Falko Skrabal, Gerhard Hannak, Harry Stuhlhofer, Elke Münzer, Egon Münzer, Gusti Münzer, Nastassja Schell, Rochus Münzer
summary: In an intimate documentary dedicated to the Austrian actress Maria Schell, her brother, filmmaker Maximilian Schell, chronicles her five-decade career as well as his personal relationship with the prolific performer. A poignant study of celebrity and family, the film follows the actress from the height of her fame in the 1950s, when she became a symbol of hope for postwar Germany, to her decline into a reclusive, debt-ridden old age.

title: The Brothers Bloom
cast: Rachel Weisz, Adrien Brody, Mark Ruffalo, Rinko Kikuchi, Robbie Coltrane, Maximilian Schell, Ricky Jay, Zachary Gordon, Max Records, Andy Nyman
summary: The Brothers Bloom made a name as the world's best con men. Now, the younger is ready to retire, but his brother lures him into one last job.

title: Savannah
cast: Jim Caviezel, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Jaimie Alexander, Bradley Whitford, Sam Shepard, Tracey Walter, Jack McBrayer, Hal Holbrook
summary: In post-Civil War America, aristocrat Ward Allen becomes a self-styled renaissance man, taking up life as a hunter and befriending a freed slave. His new rough-hewn style draws the attention of a young socialite who defies her father to be with him.

title: The Firm
cast: Tom Cruise, Jeanne Tripplehorn, Gene Hackman, Hal Holbrook, Terry Kinney, Wilford Brimley, Ed Harris, Holly Hunter, David Strathairn, Gary Busey
summary: When a Harvard Law School grad joins a prestigious firm, he ignores the warning of his wife, who fears the lucrative deal sounds too good to be true.

title: For the Boys
cast: Bette Midler, James Caan, George Segal, Patrick O'Neal, Christopher Rydell, Arye Gross, Norman Fell, Rosemary Murphy, Bud Yorkin, Dori Brenner
summary: On the eve of receiving a presidential medal, aging USO performer Dixie Leonard (Bette Midler) reflects on the events of her 50-year career. Plucked from obscurity by Eddie Sparks (James Caan), Dixie agrees to a tentative partnership that takes the duo through many wars, onstage and off. Eddie and Dixie never quite see eye to eye, but they somehow manage to keep the act together -- for the sake of the boys in uniform.

title: September
cast: Denholm Elliott, Dianne Wiest, Mia Farrow, Elaine Stritch, Sam Waterston, Jack Warden, Ira Wheeler, Jane Cecil, Rosemary Murphy
summary: Mia Farrow shines as Lane, a woman trying to recover from attempted suicide and to blot out a traumatic event from adolescence in auteur Woody Allen's Chekhovian drama.

title: Scrooged
cast: Bill Murray, Karen Allen, John Forsythe, John Glover, Bobcat Goldthwait, David Johansen, Carol Kane, Robert Mitchum, Nicholas Phillips, Michael J. Pollard
summary: Cold-hearted TV exec Bill Murray is about to discover the true meaning of Christmas -- the hard way. Director Richard Donner's wild, woolly spin on Dickens's &NFi;A Christmas Carol &NFi_;sees Murray visited by three high-spirited spirits.

title: Night of the Running Man
cast: Andrew McCarthy, Scott Glenn, John Glover, Janet Gunn, Judith Chapman, Carl Ciarfalio, Antony Ponzini, Jeanna Michaels, Don Stark, Kathrin Middleton
summary: A Las Vegas cab driver picks up a stranger who leaves a million dollars behind in the back seat -- but a hired hit man is now tracking his every move.

title: RoboCop 2
cast: Belinda Bauer, John Glover, Mario Machado, Leeza Gibbons, John Ingle, Tom Noonan, Roger Aaron Brown, Gabriel Damon, Mark Rolston, Lila Finn, John Hateley, Gage Tarrant, Thomas Rosales Jr., Brandon Smith, Wallace Merck, Peter Weller
summary: Half-machine, half-human RoboCop faces the greatest challenge of his career when he tries to rid Detroit of a deadly new designer drug.

title: Hard Lessons
cast: Denzel Washington, Lynn Whitfield, Richard Masur, Akosua Busia
summary: This drama based on a true story stars Denzel Washington as George McKenna, the tough, determined new principal of a notorious Los Angeles high school. Life is full of hard lessons for McKenna, who risks it all by going head-to-head with the drug-infested, gang-run war zone known as George Washington High.

title: The Preacher's Wife
cast: Denzel Washington, Whitney Houston, Courtney B. Vance, Gregory Hines, Jenifer Lewis, Loretta Devine, Justin Pierre Edmund, Lionel Richie, Paul Bates, Lex Monson
summary: When God overhears a church preacher despairing the potential loss of a youth center, he dispatches an angel to help him out.

title: Out of Time
cast: Denzel Washington, Eva Mendes, Sanaa Lathan, Dean Cain, John Billingsley, Robert Baker, Alex Carter, Antoni Corone, Nora Dunn
summary: The small town of Banyan Key, Fla., is shocked by a double homicide, and the beloved chief of police races against time to solve the murders.

title: Company of Heroes
cast: Tom Sizemore, Chad Michael Collins, Vinnie Jones, Dimitri Diatchenko, Neal McDonough, Sam Spruell, Richard Sammel, Melia Kreiling, Alastair Mackenzie, Jürgen Prochnow
summary: During the last major German offensive of World War II, a group of Allied soldiers sets out against all odds to turn the war around.

title: American Son
cast: Nick Cannon, Melonie Diaz, Matt O'Leary, Tom Sizemore, April Grace, Jay Hernandez, Chi McBride, Sean Marquette, Percy Daggs III, Michael Welch
summary: While home visiting relatives for Thanksgiving, 19-year-old Marine Mike Holland begins an unexpected romance, clashes with family and old friends, and confronts his fears about his imminent deployment to Iraq.

title: Strange Days
cast: Ralph Fiennes, Angela Bassett, Juliette Lewis, Tom Sizemore, Michael Wincott, Vincent D'Onofrio, Glenn Plummer, Brigitte Bako, Richard Edson, William Fichtner
summary: Ex-cop Lenny Nero is a pusher of potent (and illegal) virtual-reality clips, peddling sex and violence to the masses in Los Angeles. But when a high-profile murder shows up in his collection, Lenny finds himself ensnared in a fast-paced manhunt.

title: The Colombian Connection
cast: Tom Sizemore, Robert Thorne, Bertie Higgins, Bianca Malinowski, Kevin Anthony Brooks, Ryan Caldwell, Howard McNair, Joe Gerety, Suzanne Gutierrez, Marshall Lytle
summary: Jack Hooks is an ex-cop set up by his corrupt partner and sent to jail for a drug crime he didn't commit. Yanked out of prison with an early release deal by the DEA, he's sent on a mission to bring down the drug trade of his former partner.

title: Adult Entertainment: Disrobing an American Idol
cast: Tom Sizemore, Nina Hartley, Ron Jeremy
summary: In this documentary, nude dancers, porn stars, strip club owners and experts reflect on the positive and negative effects that the adult entertainment industry has on everyday people and society at large.

title: Black Hawk Down
cast: Josh Hartnett, Ewan McGregor, Tom Sizemore, Eric Bana, William Fichtner, Ewen Bremner, Sam Shepard, Gabriel Casseus, Orlando Bloom, Jason Isaacs
summary: Based on a true story, U.S. Rangers and an elite Delta Force team attempt to kidnap two underlings of a Somali warlord, their Black Hawk helicopters are shot down, and the Americans face intense combat with the militia on the ground.

title: Seal Team 8: Behind Enemy Lines
cast: Tom Sizemore, Lex Shrapnel, Anthony Oseyemi, Michael Everson, Darron Meyer, Aurélie Meriel, Colin Moss, Langley Kirkwood
summary: A team of U.S. Navy SEALs has only 36 hours to find a secret African mining operation and prevent the sale of weapons-grade uranium to terrorists.

title: Flight of the Intruder
cast: Danny Glover, Willem Dafoe, Brad Johnson, Rosanna Arquette, Tom Sizemore, J. Kenneth Campbell, Jared Chandler, Dann Florek, Madison Mason, Ving Rhames
summary: This action thriller follows two Navy pilots in the Vietnam War who plot to bombard Hanoi's People's Resistance Park against government orders.

title: The Snitch Cartel
cast: Manolo Cardona, Juana Acosta, Diego Cadavid, Robinson Díaz, Julián Arango, Andrés Parra, Tom Sizemore, Kuno Becker, Pedro Armendáriz Jr., Adriana Barraza, Fernando Solórzano, Juan Pablo Raba
summary: Struggling to rise above his working-class origins, Martin Gonzalez begins selling drugs for the brutal North Valley Cartel.

title: Roger Dodger
cast: Campbell Scott, Jesse Eisenberg, Isabella Rossellini, Elizabeth Berkley, Jennifer Beals, Mina Badie, Ben Shenkman, Chris Stack, Gabriel Millman, Colin Fickes
summary: A cynical advertising copywriter tries to teach his teenage nephew the art of manipulating women, but his seemingly foolproof methods unravel.

title: Flashdance
cast: Jennifer Beals, Michael Nouri, Lilia Skala, Sunny Johnson, Kyle T. Heffner, Lee Ving, Ron Karabatsos, Belinda Bauer, Robert Wuhl
summary: Alex works as a welder by day and a stripper by night, but she dreams of training at the local conservatory and becoming a professional dancer. Meanwhile, she navigates a romance with her boss at the steelyard.

title: The Prophecy 2
cast: Christopher Walken, Russell Wong, Jennifer Beals, Brittany Murphy, Eric Roberts, Glenn Danzig, Steve Hytner, Bruce Abbott, Danny Strong, Elizabeth Dennehy
summary: Kicked out of his asylum in hell, fallen angel Gabriel continues his revolution, in which bad angels seek to destroy good ones -- along with all humanity. The only hope for deliverance is the unborn child of nurse Valerie Rosales.

title: The Thief and the Cobbler
cast: Vincent Price, Matthew Broderick, Jennifer Beals, Eric Bogosian, Toni Collette, Jonathan Winters, Bobbi Page, Clive Revill, Kevin Dorsey, Stanley Baxter
summary: In this colorful animated fantasy, a modest cobbler who pines for a beautiful princess has a chance to win her heart by doing battle with an evil sorcerer and saving her father's kingdom from a marauding army of one-eyed warriors.

title: Wishful Thinking
cast: Drew Barrymore, Jennifer Beals, James Le Gros, Jon Stewart, Mel Gorham, Eric Thal, Desiree Casado, Lázaro Pérez
summary: When Max meets Elizabeth, there's a connection, but when Elizabeth starts talking marriage, Max pushes her away. Meanwhile, Elizabeth's friendship with Jack makes Max jealous, and Max's co-worker Lena jumps at the chance to win Max for herself.

title: Four Rooms
cast: Tim Roth, Antonio Banderas, Jennifer Beals, Bruce Willis, Paul Calderon, Madonna, Marisa Tomei, Quentin Tarantino, Ione Skye, Lili Taylor
director: Quentin Tarantino, Robert Rodriguez, Allison Anders, Alexandre Rockwell
summary: One mad New Year's Eve, an overwhelmed bellboy copes with witches and diabolical children, gets caught in the middle of a sour relationship and settles a bloody bet for members of a superstar's entourage.

title: The Chicago Code
cast: Jason Clarke, Jennifer Beals, Matt Lauria, Devin Kelley, Todd Williams, Billy Lush, Delroy Lindo, Paolina Cimino
summary: Newly appointed police superintendant Teresa Colvin and her former partner, veteran detective Jarek Wysocki, battle to rid Chicago of crime as well as the rampant corruption of powerful politico Ronin Gibbons in this gritty cop drama.

title: The L Word
cast: Jennifer Beals, Leisha Hailey, Laurel Holloman, Mia Kirshner, Katherine Moennig, Pam Grier, Rachel Shelley, Daniela Sea, Erin Daniels, Marlee Matlin
summary: This trailblazing cable series follows the tangled lives and ever-changing relationships among a close-knit group of lesbians -- including a lusty hairstylist and a recovering alcoholic -- who call Los Angeles home.

title: The Bride
cast: Sting, Jennifer Beals, Anthony Higgins, Clancy Brown, David Rappaport, Geraldine Page, Alexei Sayle, Phil Daniels, Veruschka von Lehndorff, Quentin Crisp
summary: Frankenstein and his creations need a place in the world: lovely Eva must declare her sexual independence while her grotesque mate gains self-esteem.

title: Cinemanovels
cast: Lauren Lee Smith, Jennifer Beals, Ben Cotton, Sarah Grey, Katharine Isabelle, Kett Turton, Viv Leacock, Gabrielle Rose, Jerry Wasserman, Erica Carroll
summary: As a young woman prepares a retrospective of her recently deceased director father's work, his movies begin to affect her in unexpected ways.

title: Caribe
cast: John Savage, Kara Glover, Stephen McHattie, Sam Malkin, Zack Nesis, Paul Koslo, Maury Chaykin, T.J. Scott
summary: Prepare to get tangled in the jungles of Belize when an arms smuggler loses her partner in a deadly shootout and finds herself on the run in the tropics of Central America.  Helen is an amateur, making her money as an illegal arms trader to Central American terrorists.

title: Mouse Hunt
cast: Nathan Lane, Lee Evans, Vicki Lewis, Maury Chaykin, Eric Christmas, Michael Jeter, Debra Christofferson, Camilla Søeberg, Christopher Walken
summary: Two down-on-their-luck brothers inherit a run-down mansion that turns out to be worth millions. They can sell it and pocket a fortune, but first they have to evict its diminutive tenant: a mouse with no intention of leaving.

title: Jerry and Tom
cast: Joe Mantegna, Sam Rockwell, Maury Chaykin, Ted Danson, Charles Durning, William H. Macy, Peter Riegert, Sarah Polley, Shelley Cook
summary: Easygoing family man Tom (Joe Mantegna) -- used-car salesman by day, mob enforcer by night -- shows his brash co-worker Jerry (Sam Rockwell) the ropes of contract killing. Soon the young apprentice not only gets the hang of it but begins to enjoy killing strangers for money. For his directorial debut, Saul Rubinek assembled a formidable supporting cast that includes William H. Macy, Ted Danson and Charles Durning.

title: Camilla
cast: Jessica Tandy, Bridget Fonda, Elias Koteas, Graham Greene, Hume Cronyn, Maury Chaykin
summary: Camilla is a heartwarming comedy about two women (Jessica Tandy and Bridget Fonda) who become fast friends and hit the road for the adventure of a lifetime. While a confused husband, a desperate son, and a long-lost love frantically try to track them down, the women find themselves in some funny situations, including losing their car in a lake, being duped by a con man, and staging a kidnapping.

title: Wilby Wonderful
cast: James Allodi, Maury Chaykin, Paul Gross, Rebecca Jenkins, Sandra Oh, Ellen Page, Callum Keith Rennie, Daniel MacIvor, Susannah Hoffman
summary: Within 24 hours at a sleepy Nova Scotia community, a town scandal looms on the horizon; a store clerk repeatedly attempts suicide (even as a handyman repeatedly interrupts him); and an uptight real estate agent drifts apart from her husband, a cop.

title: The Hunt for the BTK Killer
cast: Robert Forster, Michael Michele, Maury Chaykin, Mimi Kuzyk, Gregg Henry, Johnie Chase, Martha Irving, Nigel Bennett, Hollis McLaren, Andrew Airlie
summary: This chilling fact-based drama chronicles the story of Dennis Rader, who was dubbed the BTK killer because he bound, tortured and killed his victims. Rader murdered 10 people in Wichita, Kan. -- and remained at large for more than 30 years.

title: NYC 22
cast: Adam Goldberg, Leelee Sobieski, Stark Sands, Judy Marte, Harold House Moore, Tom Reed, Felix Solis, Terry Kinney
summary: Six rookie cops hit the streets of Manhattan, juggling their personal lives with their new responsibilities as keepers of the peace. The diverse group struggles with newbie mistakes under the guidance of their tough field training officer.

title: Canterbury's Law
cast: Julianna Margulies, Ben Shenkman, Keith Robinson, Trieste Dunn, Terry Kinney, Aidan Quinn
summary: Julianna Margulies stars in this drama as spirited attorney Elizabeth Canterbury, a woman who balances her desire to help others seek justice with her own ongoing struggle to deal with her son's unsolved disappearance.

title: A Life Less Ordinary
cast: Ewan McGregor, Cameron Diaz, Holly Hunter, Delroy Lindo, Dan Hedaya, Ian McNeice, Frank Kanig, Mel Winkler, Stanley Tucci, Anne Cullimore Decker
summary: Determined to live "a life less ordinary," Robert (Ewan McGregor), a down-and-out janitor, kidnaps narcissistic heiress Celine (Cameron Diaz) in hopes of pulling in a big ransom. Unfortunately for Robert, Celine embraces her life as a captive and enjoys Robert's bungling attempt at retrieving a payoff. Add two angels (Delroy Lindo and Holly Hunter) who try to make Robert and Celine fall in love, and the situation becomes extraordinary.

title: Pumpkin
cast: Christina Ricci, Hank Harris, Brenda Blethyn, Dominique Swain, Marisa Coughlan, Sam Ball, Harry Lennix, Nina Foch, Caroline Aaron, Lisa Banes
summary: A perky sorority sister is assigned to coach a young man named Pumpkin, a mentally challenged athlete who ultimately touches her heart.

title: Tiger Woods Story
cast: Keith David, Khalil Kain, Freda Foh Shen, Gary Leroi Gray, T.J. Hall, John Cho, David Grant Wright, Kathryne Dora Brown, Albert Hall
summary: With his father coaching him and his mother providing a strong spiritual influence, Tiger Woods rose to fame and fortune. But his success came at a price, as he endured personal struggles with racism, self-doubt and cultural identity.

title: Ally McBeal
cast: Calista Flockhart, Greg Germann, Jane Krakowski, Peter MacNicol, Portia de Rossi, Lucy Liu, Courtney Thorne-Smith, Lisa Nicole Carson, Vonda Shepard, Albert Hall

The agency quickly hires the overnight heroes for its new campaign -- which turns out to be as successful as it is tasteless. Dick Shawn's send-up of talk-show host Phil Donahue is a must-see.

But in the process, they open up their valley to evil outsiders and Littlefoot ends up lost in the frightening Great Beyond.

The escalating feud results in bloodshed, but the tides turn when a mysterious man (James Mason) washes ashore and takes the family's side in this period drama.

Al Menetti (Judd Hirsch) -- the lead detective on the case -- refuse to give up hope in this well-acted drama also starring David Dukes and Stockard Channing.

Don Ameche reprises his Oscar-winning role along with Wilford Brimley, Hume Cronyn, Gwen Verdon, Maureen Stapleton and Jessica Tandy.

Goaded by her best friend, Roslyn embarks on a dangerous affair, threatening her marriage, her reputation and life as she knows it.

Whether revenge will be sweet -- or bittersweet -- is anyone's guess.

Heyst saves Alma from this terrible fate and they escape to a remote island, but the German sends the sinister Mr. Jones (Sam Neill) and his bandits to hunt them down.

Curious, Fisk delivers a case of the stuff to the dean, regaling in the man's stories about his previous life as a dog. Peter O'Toole co-stars in this offbeat British comedy.

But when Sybylla falls for affluent landowner Harry Beecham (Sam Neill), she must choose between traditional marriage and pursuing her career ambitions.
